cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for pedestrian detection, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a Graph Convolutional Network (GCN) to capture inter and intra-part co-occurrence information, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method on two challenging datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of the topological structure of the pedestrian and the absence of part-based annotations or additional visible bounding-box (VBB) information suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques for pedestrian detection, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
